==English==

===Etymology===
[[fall]] + [[back]]

===Noun===
'''fallback'''
# A [[backup]] plan or [[contingency]] strategy; an alternative which can be used if something goes wrong with the main plan.
#: ''As a fallback, I suppose we can use typewriters if the word processing system fails.''

